{"name":"Heresy (Cleric)","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Cleric Adjustments:</strong> You retain your divine font, but you must @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.OSefkMgojBLqmRDh]{Refocus} after each time you @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} from your divine font before you can cast another. You can prepare any combination of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.wdA52JJnsuQWeyqz]{Harm}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.rfZpqmj0AIIdkVIs]{Heal}, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.gKKqvLohtrSJj3BM]{Magic Missile} as divine spells in your divine font, regardless of your deity’s actual font.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"heresy-cleric","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":0},"traits":{"value":["cleric"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741168351,"modifiedTime":1685743398304,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"4leHvD4nro4ZZ4ts"}
{"name":"Rush of Apostacy","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>A creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.nlCjDvLMf2EkV2dl]{Quickened} by your healing spell.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.nlCjDvLMf2EkV2dl]{Quickened} until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p>You can use the extra action to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.UHpkTuCtyaPqiCAB]{Step}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Bcxarzksqt9ezrs6]{Stride}, or as part of casting a divine spell.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"rush-of-apostacy","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["archetype","necromancy"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Heretic Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741303763,"modifiedTime":1685755899110,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"6QuNrF8EuYsMDG9S"}
{"name":"Heretic Dedication","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Access</strong> You have grievously failed at one or more of your deity’s edicts or committed one or more of their anathemas.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You have violated your deity's teachings and find yourself at the fringe of the faith community. You become trained in Deception (or expert if you were already trained). Choose a common divine spell up to half your level when you take this feat. You gain this spell as a divine innate spell you can cast once per day, heightened up to half your level rounded up. You gain the heresy class feature. If your class or archetype isn't mentioned under Heresy, work with your GM to determine appropriate adjustments to your class features.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Special</strong> You cannot select another dedication feat until you have gained two other feats from the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-magic-journals.6DPJqrJJBdYR5hbz.JournalEntryPage.xGaXbWsvd02vMHPg]{Heretic} archetype.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.skills.dec.rank","value":1},{"key":"GrantItem","allowDuplicate":false,"uuid":"Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.ai3NkgFp9adQ3kFI"}],"slug":"heretic-dedication","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["archetype","class","dedication"],"rarity":"uncommon"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"You gain class benefits from a deity or other divine entity. This usually means your class is champion, cleric, or oracle, or you have a multiclass archetype for one of them."}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741149950,"modifiedTime":1685755300842,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"92InfRw3HGfCHPzy"}
{"name":"Heresy (Champion)","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Champion Adjustments:</strong> You lose your champion’s reaction and instead gain the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-actions.howTtrcMDPR16l3h]{Heretical Word} reaction.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"onDeleteActions":{"grantee":"restrict"},"key":"GrantItem","allowDuplicate":false,"uuid":"Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-actions.howTtrcMDPR16l3h"}],"slug":"heresy-champion","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":0},"traits":{"value":["champion"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741168351,"modifiedTime":1685743375808,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"B9pXfsdOyXnl0kpy"}
{"name":"Heresy (Oracle)","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Oracle Adjustments:</strong> Your heresy domain spells don’t gain the cursebound trait, and therefore don’t advance your curse when you cast them. When you make your daily preparations, in addition to your mystery’s revelation spell, you gain another focus spell of your GM’s choosing until your next daily preparations. This focus spell has the cursebound trait.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"heresy-oracle","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":0},"traits":{"value":["oracle"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741168351,"modifiedTime":1685743455211,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"C7c8AvxWUk4VZ8x9"}
{"name":"Creed Revision","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.dGFQvkDRmyvvf4IQ]{Splinter Faith} class feat without needing to retrain, and you gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.hT4INKGtly4QY8KN]{Domain Initiate} with one of your selected domains’ focus spells.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"key":"GrantItem","allowDuplicate":false,"uuid":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.dGFQvkDRmyvvf4IQ"},{"key":"GrantItem","allowDuplicate":false,"uuid":"Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.hT4INKGtly4QY8KN"}],"slug":"creed-revision","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Heretic Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741303763,"modifiedTime":1685755800950,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"OS0jMMSqliaVRNAp"}
{"name":"Part the Veil","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You spend 10 minutes and open your mind to new avenues of knowledge taboo to your faith. Ask about a particular course of action. This activity can predict results up to 30 minutes into the future and reveals your GM’s best guess between the following outcomes: </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Unveiled </strong>The course of action will likely reveal useful information to you. </li>\n<li><strong>Veiled </strong>The course of action may or may not reveal useful information to you.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Your GM rolls a secret @Check[type:flat|dc:6|traits:secret] check. On a failure, the result is always “Veiled.” This makes it impossible to tell whether a “Veiled” result is accurate. If anyone asks about the same topic on a subsequent use of this feat, your GM uses the secret roll result from the first use. If circumstances change, though, it’s possible to get a different result.</p>\n<p>If you are legendary in Religion, you take only 1 minute to @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.WeGt18poda54pPrK]{Part the Veil}.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"part-the-veil","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype","divination","exploration","prediction"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Heretic Dedication"},{"value":"expert in Religion"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741303763,"modifiedTime":1685755841415,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"WeGt18poda54pPrK"}
{"name":"Heresy","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Your relationship with your deity has become strained or severed. However, you have served long enough to eke out a remnant of their benefits, or you are beginning to draw divine power from a different source. As such, some of your divine power is weaker, but you invest your own conviction into your magic. You retain your divine spellcasting. Whenever you cast a divine spell that restores Hit Points, reduce the dice size by 1 step and any static amount by 2 (minimum 0). Each target who regains Hit Points from your divine spells becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.nlCjDvLMf2EkV2dl]{Quickened} until the end of their next turn and can use the extra action to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.UHpkTuCtyaPqiCAB]{Step} or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Bcxarzksqt9ezrs6]{Stride}.</p>\n<p>If you have any domain spells from your deity, you lose them and gain the corresponding heresy domain spells, instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Champion Adjustments:</strong> @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.B9pXfsdOyXnl0kpy]{Heresy (Champion)}</p>\n<p><strong>Cleric Adjustments:</strong> @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.4leHvD4nro4ZZ4ts]{Heresy (Cleric)}</p>\n<p><strong>Oracle Adjustments: </strong>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.C7c8AvxWUk4VZ8x9]{Heresy (Oracle)}</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"adjustName":false,"key":"ChoiceSet","choices":[{"label":"Champion","value":"Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.B9pXfsdOyXnl0kpy"},{"label":"Cleric","value":"Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.4leHvD4nro4ZZ4ts"},{"label":"Oracle","value":"Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.C7c8AvxWUk4VZ8x9"}],"flag":"heresyClass","prompt":"Choose your class"},{"key":"GrantItem","allowDuplicate":false,"uuid":"{item|flags.pf2e.rulesSelections.heresyClass}"}],"slug":"heresy","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":0},"traits":{"value":[],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685742456181,"modifiedTime":1685756189420,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"ai3NkgFp9adQ3kFI"}
{"name":"Heterodoxy","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recall Knowledge} about a creature within 60 feet and received two pieces of information. If you @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recalled Knowledge} about a type of creature and more than one of them is within range, choose an individual among the group.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You speak aloud the information you recalled. If one of the pieces of information was incorrect, it becomes true for that creature for 10 minutes.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"heterodoxy","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Dubious Knowledge"},{"value":"Heretic Dedication"}]},"location":null,"frequency":{"max":1,"per":"day"}},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741303763,"modifiedTime":1685755957077,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"eHgTxgSfxWkEKky3"}
{"name":"Reformer","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Access </strong>Through study, public debate, or travel among the planes, you have proven your heresy to be true and in accordance with your deity’s will for their followers.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Any limitations imposed by your heresy class feature are removed, including the dice size and static amounts involved in your healing spells and needing to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.OSefkMgojBLqmRDh]{Refocus} between casting spells from your divine font. You regain any class features or feats you lost due to your @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-faith-heretic.ai3NkgFp9adQ3kFI]{Heresy}, such as losing your champion’s reaction or losing domain spells. You also gain @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.hT4INKGtly4QY8KN]{Domain Initiate} and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.uR44wELN9OlU68cL]{Advanced Domain} for one domain that thematically matches your new orthodoxy.</p>\n<p>Taking this feat has serious repercussions for your adventure’s world, so work with your GM to make appropriate adjustments to the structure of your faith, as well as how far your reformation spreads.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"reformer","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":16},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"rare"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Heretic Dedication"},{"value":"legendary in Religion"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741303763,"modifiedTime":1685755954891,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"yMR4IGvyhKkstD88"}
{"name":"Splinter Following","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Access </strong>You have acquired followers for your heresy from your original faith. You might be the direct leader of a congregation, a consultant for a splinter group, or a colleague among a group of heterodox scholars.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Your heresy's followers are helpful to you, allowing you to make simple @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.DCb62iCBrJXy0Ik6]{Requests} of them such as purchasing basic equipment with your funds or finding a room at an inn. These followers do not travel with you to places that are obviously dangerous, including most adventure locations, but they'll wait for you at the nearest settlement. Your heresy's followers never use actions in encounter mode other than to retreat, and they abandon you if you intentionally bring them harm or at your GM's discretion. When you @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.plBGdZhqq5JBl1D8]{Gather Information}, you can use these followers to assist you, allowing you to attempt a Religion check instead of Diplomacy for this activity. When you succeed using this assistance, you also gain a +2 circumstance bonus on Intimidation checks within that settlement for 1 week.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"splinter-following","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":7},"traits":{"value":["archetype","skill"],"rarity":"uncommon"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Heretic Dedication"},{"value":"Splinter Faith"},{"value":"master in Diplomacy or Religion"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741303763,"modifiedTime":1685755876658,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"ydtVpVcd1ti5gssl"}
{"name":"On the Run","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You can move your full Speed while using @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.SB7cMECVtE06kByk]{Cover Tracks}, and you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your Survival DC when using @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.SB7cMECVtE06kByk]{Cover Tracks}.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"on-the-run","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":5},"traits":{"value":["archetype","skill"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Heretic Dedication"},{"value":"expert in Survival"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.6","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685741303763,"modifiedTime":1685755958466,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"yrcJrL4aQIL94P39"}
